        <note rend="SCRIPT">
          <p>Gothic, written in 2 columns of 35-40 lines, 1 scribe</p>
        </note>
        <note rend="ARTISTS">
          <p>2 artists (1st responsible for miniatures up to 8v, 2nd for those after 10r)</p>
        </note>
        <note rend="DECORATION">
          <p>2 single-column miniatures in colors and gold accompanied by decorated initials in pink, blue and gold, and a 3-sided foliate bar border containing a hybrid creature (f. <locus>1r</locus>). 17 single-column miniatures in black, brown, pink and green (ff. 2r (x2), 3r, 4r, 5r, 7r, 8v, 10v, 12r, 13v, 15r, 15v, 21v, 24v, 25v, 28r, 31r); at least 5 empty spaces left for miniatures (ff. 44r, 49r, 49v, 51v, 55v). Gold initials (2 with foliate extenders) on pink and blue ground throughout. Figures in grisaille on ff. <locus>2r</locus>, <locus>3r</locus>, <locus>4r</locus>, <locus>5r</locus>, <locus>7r</locus>.</p>
        </note>
        <note rend="DIMENSIONS">
          <p>350 x 263 mm (this measurement is from Langlois)</p>
        </note>
        <note rend="FOLIATION">
          <p>ff. ii + 145 + ii</p>
        </note>
        <note rend="BINDING">
          <p>French; panelled calf binding painted blue with gilt fillet border on upper and lower covers, raised spine bands, marbled endpapers.</p>
        </note>
        <note rend="PROVENANCE">
          <p> Pierre (1582-1651) and Jacques (1591-1656) Du Puy, 1st half of 17th century - it was ms. no 11 in their collection - bequethed to royal library in 1656; 18th century stamp of Bibliotheca Regiae (royal library), where it was ms. 7200 (ff. <locus>1r</locus>, <locus>144v</locus>)</p>
        </note>
        <note rend="SELECT BIBLIOGRAPHY">
          <p>1. Paulin Paris, <hi rend="italics">Les manuscrits françois de la Bibliothèque du roi</hi> (Paris: Techener, 1836-1848), IV, p. 238</p>
          <p>2. Langlois, <hi rend="italics">Les manuscrits</hi>, p. 12</p>
        </note>
